import { Box, Button, IconButton, List, ListItem, ListItemText } from '@material-ui/core'
import { Close } from '@material-ui/icons'
import React from 'react'
import useStyles from './SidebarElement'
const Sidebar = ({isOpen , toggle}) => {
    const classes = useStyles()
    return (
        <>
            <Box isOpen={isOpen} onClick={toggle} className={
                isOpen? classes.box : classes.unbox
            } display={{ xs:'block' ,sm:'block' , md:'none'}}>
                <IconButton className={classes.iconbutton}>
                    <Close className={classes.close} />
                </IconButton>
                <List className={classes.list}>
                    <ListItem >
                        <ListItemText className={classes.listitem} primary='HOME'/>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <ListItemText className={classes.listitem} primary='SERVICES'/>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <ListItemText className={classes.listitem} primary='CONTACT'/>
                    </ListItem>
                    <ListItem>
                        <ListItemText className={classes.listitem} primary='ABOUT'/>
                    </ListItem>                               
                </List>
                <Box display='flex' justifyContent='center'>
                <Button variant='contained' className={classes.button}>SIGN UP</Button>
                </Box>
            
            </Box>
        </>
    )
}

export default Sidebar
